title.44: Combat Kelly and the Deadly Dozen (1972) #1

description.0: Captain America and the Falcon in: Terror in the Night! Mr. Hyde and Scorpion continue the assault on our heroes!
description.6: The Hulk! Sub-Mariner! Dr. Strange! Together again, against the man called Necrodamus! An off-beat read!
description.7: Only death lies on the ocean floor in “Dead Man’s Escape!”
description.8: Death in the wind-lashed sky! Electro and Killgrave gang up against the Man Without Fear! Plus, will the Widow accept Daredevil’s help when the chips are down?
description.12: Spidey and the Torch are back at it again! But can they contend with the terrible power of MORBIUS, the Living Vampire?
description.13: Spider-Man faces off against the Gibbon!
description.14: When Sporadik, a famed Russian chess player, dies from a sudden heart attack, the Avengers suspect foul-play. Featuring Thor in his alter-ego guise of Dr. Donald Blake!
description.15: Mr. Hyde strikes again! The Scorpion hangs loose! Get ready for panic on Park Avenue!
description.17: The Hulk on trial! And Matt Murdock's for the defense! Plus, check out a handful of guest-witnesses- all faces you've seen before!
description.18: Iron Man takes on his deadliest foe yet! Enter Firbrand! Will Tony Stark survive the fury and inferno this new villain brings? Don't miss out as Iron Man puts everything on the line in this epic battle!
description.19: A mysterious enemy enters Doctor Strange's Sanctum Sanctorum...but before the good doctor knows it, the entire Sanctum is transported to another dimension!
description.21: The wondrous wind-up to the battle for the soul of Odin! Heimdall's mysterious quest on earth! All this, and Ego Prime too!
description.23: From the stars he first came- and now he returns, to menace the earth as never before. The Monster of the Lost Lagoon emerges.
description.25: Mastermind has gathered the Blob & Unus to form the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants!
description.27: Killgrave, the Purple Man, is back, and DD may never be the same again. That is, if he lives! Plus, Black Widow's secret past.
description.29: The Hulk- captured and held for trial! And the lawyer's name is...Matt Murdock! Sound familiar?
description.30: The birth of the power! The origin of the Golden Avenger is revealed!
description.32: The Day of Ragnarok as you've never seen it before! What can even the gods do when the end of the universe is at hand?
description.33: Galactus! The Silver Surfer! The fabulous FF! All cavorting and clashing in perhaps the greatest battle-issue yet!
description.34: Peter Parker has been taken hostage...by Spider-Man?
description.35: Will the Avengers accept aid from Swordsman, a disgraced former member of the team? When an amnesiac Hercules is captured by Ares, the Avengers must call on teammates past and present to save the fallen hero.
description.36: Captain America and the Falcon are trapped in the Bottles of Death by the new, super-powerful Stranger!
description.37: A plant-monster strikes out against a farmer after gaining sentience! And their rampage is only growing…
description.41: The First Full Appearance of the Darkhold, also know as the Book of the Damned!  Werewolf by Night finds himself upon the Isle of the Damned!
description.42: Who or what is Xemnu? Can the Defenders discover his true plot?
description.46: DD and the Widow hit San Francisco! And nobody's minding the welcome wagon…all but Electro! A titanic turning-point issue for Natasha and Matt.
description.50: The Amazing Spider-Man and the Human Torch in another team-up for the ages! This time, they're up against the menace of the FRIGHTFUL FOUR!
description.53: Spider-Man fights the Monks of the Light and their leader the Giant One.
description.54: While attempting to restore the memories of Hercules in order to learn what his prophecies of doom could be, Hawkeye fills the Avengers in on how he returned to Earth and found Hercules.
description.55: Captain American and the Falcon take on Batroc's Brigade!
description.56: A predatory being has been lurking in a man’s dreams… and those dreams are now reality!
description.57: They call it the Crawling Unknown! And it's the one thing so loathsome, so mind-shattering, that even ol' Greenskin can't stop it! Plus, will Bruce Banner find a way to be reunited with his true love, Jarella?
description.58: Tony Stark and Iron Man backs are against the wall, when the Iron Playboy is being attacked from all angles. Will Stark find balance between being a super hero and a businessman?
description.59: Warlock vs. Rhodan and the Hounds of Helios! A divine battle fit for the gods!
description.61: The legions of Pluto battle the hordes of Hela- for the soul of all-father Odin. And Thor must choose between them. A raucous battle of the gods!
description.63: Things are just winding up! The Silver Surfer teams up with the FF. But how long can even they survive against the combined power of Gabriel...and Galactus?
description.64: The Beast is back - and Iron Man's after him! Plus - more secrets behind the mutant that walks like a man - and looks like a monster!
description.65: Remember the ominous Ox? Well, he's back, and so is the breathtaking Black Widow! But they'd both better hurry; DD's leaving New York!
description.68: The return of the X-Man Havok! The magnetic might of Polaris! Plus, Hulk goes on a rampage, just as the military closes in.
description.69: Introducing the power of Warlock! Who is this near-celestial being endowed with abilities beyond any human? His origin revealed, in his first ever appearance!
description.71: The Death of Odin! And before Asgard can recover, re-enter Tana Nile and her sinister Colonizers!
description.72: Gabriel has blown his horn and the earth faces an apocalypse! The FF battles as never before...but then, you've gotta see that for yourself!
description.73: Spider-Man faces off against the upgraded Spider-Slayer. And if he survives this bout, he'll have a few words for J. Jonah Jameson when he's done...
description.74: Now that the Avengers have sorted out the war between the Kree-Skrull Empire, they must turn to the next order of business - locate the missing Avenger, Goliath!
description.75: Battling the Kingpin in the Las Vegas suite of mysterious industrialist Harold Howard, the Red, White, and Blue Avengers and the Fighting Falcon are suddenly stunned by the senses-shattering sight of the Red Skull!
description.82: Mile-high madness, as the Man Without Fear battles the power-packed Gladiator...in the deadly skies!
description.83: He is called The Inheritor. And what he claims as his birthright is nothing less than...planet earth! Will Hulk be able to subdue this empowered adversary? Plus, learn of The Inheritor's strange beginnings!
description.84: Iron Man continues his fight with the Night Phantom robot and destroys it. Meanwhile, Simon Gilbert addresses the Stark Industries board of directors criticizing Tony Stark's negligence towards the company. Will Tony be kicked out of his own company?
description.86: Who could possibly smash Thor, Odin, and all the hosts of Asgard? No one but Mangog! The Warriors Three provide necessary backup.
description.87: They call their mysterious new foe...the Air-Walker- yet, wait'll you find out who he really is!
description.88: Spencer Smyth has learned the secret identity of Peter Parker!
description.89: While Cap and the SHIELD Femme Force battle to destroy the forces of Hydra in an underground fortress near Las Vegas, a sinister figure watches the melee and prepares to press the button which will destroy the combatants on both sides...
description.92: Spider-Man and the Human Torch team up in this Christmas special to fight the perils of the Sandman!
description.94: The Beast, otherwise known as Dr. Hank McCoy, is featured for the first time in his furry form! And is taking on a solo adventure! Check it out!
description.95: Followers of the Dread Dormammu kidnap Dr. Strange to use him as a sacrifice to allow Dormammu access to Earth. Luckily the Defenders unite to tackle Dormammu and his demonic followers.
description.98: Spencer Smyth builds J. Jonah Jameson a new Spider-Slayer robot, but JJJ doesn't know that Smyth has his own plans for the hunting-killing machine.
description.99: Last issue, Steve Rogers' world was shaken to the core. Will the Star Spangled Avenger finally put an end to HYDRA? Or will anger consume him in his pursuit for revenge? Plus, find out who's been pulling the strings all along!

2.text: When his Hero for Hire service falls short, Luke Cage goes looking for an office. While searching, he is attacked by hit men hired by Diamond Back! Luke Cage exacts revenge. If he can bring Diamond Back to the authorities, he may be able to wipe his record clean and live as a fully free man. But Diamond Back won't go down without a really good fight!

3.text: Ka-Zar vs. the misanthropic Man-Thing! And when A.I.M. drops in, to boot - look out!

5.text: The most powerful mutant of all returns! Don't miss the deadly challenge of…Sunfire!

8.text: Death in the wind-lashed sky! Electro and Killgrave gang up against the Man Without Fear! Plus, will the Widow accept Daredevil’s help when the chips are down?

11.text: The return of Prince Byrrah, pretender to the throne of Atlantis! Plus, the baneful Badoon!

12.text: Spidey and the Torch are back at it again! But can they contend with the terrible power of MORBIUS, the Living Vampire?

22.text: Frank Drake has lost everything, including the woman he loves. On the verge of suicide, Frank is visited by someone who has wanted to meet him for some time, someone who may be able to help him enact his revenge!

26.text: Ant-Man is working on an experimental drug with his new research assistant: a bright young man named Peter Parker.

27.text: Killgrave, the Purple Man, is back, and DD may never be the same again. That is, if he lives! Plus, Black Widow's secret past.

38.text: Terror in the Everglades! Perhaps the greatest Ka-Zar saga of all, as the jungle lord comes face-to-face with…the Man-Thing!

40.text: The scourge of the seas returns to his abandoned Antarctic home- to find it deserted no longer! And then…Prince Byrrah!

41.text: Werewolf by Night finds himself upon the Isle of the Damned!

43.text: A wrongfully charged inmate in Seagate Prison named Carl Lucas undergoes a scientific experiment. When a racist prison guard tampers with the machine, Lucas develops some supernatural side-effects! Namely, enhanced strength and bulletproof skin! Luke Cage is born.

46.text: DD and the Widow hit San Francisco! And nobody's minding the welcome wagon…all but Electro! A titanic turning-point issue for Natasha and Matt.

49.text: This is it! The fearful finale to the three-way war between Namor, MODOK, and a desperate Doctor Doom!

50.text: The Amazing Spider-Man and the Human Torch in another team-up for the ages! This time, they're up against the menace of the FRIGHTFUL FOUR!

51.text: A teenager by day -- a "Werewolf By Night"! Yet, can even a man-beast survive against the steel claw of Kraig?

62.text: Count Dracula has turned the woman Frank loves into a vampire. Swearing revenge, Frank sets out to take Count Dracula down!

65.text: Remember the ominous Ox? Well, he's back, and so is the breathtaking Black Widow! But they'd both better hurry; DD's leaving New York!

66.text: Frank Drake, the descendant of Count Dracula, has inherited the Count's castle. With a plan to turn the castle into a tourist hot-spot, Frank sets out for Transylvania. But something dark lurks in the bowels of Castle Dracula!

77.text: Namor -- Dr. Doom -- and the murderous MODOK makes three! The quest for the Cosmic Cube builds to a mind-staggering climax!

81.text: Rick Jones is transported from the Negative Zone to the Kree homeworld by the Supreme Intellgence itself. When Ronan and his men arrive to eliminate Jones and the Supreme Intelligence, Rick's newfound power manifests for the first time!

Rick Jones is transported from the Negative Zone to the Kree homeworld by the Supreme Intellgence itself. When Ronan and his men arrive to eliminate Jones and the Supreme Intelligence, Rick's newfound power manifests for the first time!

82.text: Mile-high madness, as the Man Without Fear battles the power-packed Gladiator...in the deadly skies!

91.text: Doctor Doom! MODOK! The calamitous Cosmic Cube! And Namor -- with his memory gone!

97.text: The Avengers travel to the Andromeda Galaxy aboard a S.H.I.E.L.D. spacecraft to rescue their captured teammates. En route to the faraway sector of the universe, the Avengers are attacked by a Skrull flotilla!
